  @* ── Step 3 · Monuments (sidebar: block icons, header "Wool monuments") ─── *@
  <article class="ds-example">
    <div class="ds-example-label">Step 3 of 4 — Monuments</div>
    <div class="flow-bar">
      <div class="flow-steps">
        <button class="flow-step flow-step--done"><i data-lucide="check"></i>Colours</button>
        <button class="flow-step flow-step--done"><i data-lucide="check"></i>Spawn</button>
        <button class="flow-step flow-step--active">Monuments</button>
        <button class="flow-step">Room</button>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-bar-actions">
        <button class="action-btn">Back</button>
        <button class="action-btn action-btn--primary">Next: Room</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ds-workspace-frame">
      <div class="workspace">
        <div class="workspace-sidebar">
          <div class="workspace-scroll">
            <section class="panel-section">
              <div class="section-header section-header--ruled">
                <h2 class="section-title">Wool monuments</h2>
                <span class="badge badge--warning">2 to place</span>
              </div>
              <p class="section-desc">Place wools − 1 = 3 monuments on blue's side — one per enemy team. Orbit copies the <em>positions</em> 1:1 to the other wools, but the <em>capturing team is derived</em>: a wool is captured by its three enemies, never its own (dashed = orbited).</p>
              <div class="panel-list">
                <div class="list-row list-row--compact list-row--selected"><span class="geo-type-icon" style="color:#55FF55"><i data-lucide="square"></i></span><span class="list-label list-label--mono">blue-green</span></div>
                <div class="list-row list-row--compact list-row--muted"><span class="geo-type-icon"><i data-lucide="square-dashed"></i></span><span class="list-label">Unassigned</span><span class="badge badge--dim">place</span></div>
                <div class="list-row list-row--compact list-row--muted"><span class="geo-type-icon"><i data-lucide="square-dashed"></i></span><span class="list-label">Unassigned</span><span class="badge badge--dim">place</span></div>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar-handle"></div>
        <div class="workspace-canvas">
          <div class="canvas-subbar">
            <div class="canvas-toolbar">
              <button class="draw-tool-btn" title="Pan"><i data-lucide="hand"></i></button>
              <button class="draw-tool-btn draw-tool-btn--active" title="Place monument block"><i data-lucide="square"></i></button>
            </div>
            <div class="subbar-sep"></div>
            <button class="filter-chip filter-chip--active" title="Orbit fill active">Orbit</button>
            <span class="canvas-cursor">X 72 · Z 18</span>
            <div class="canvas-subbar-right">
              <button class="draw-tool-btn" title="Fit island"><i data-lucide="maximize-2"></i></button>
              <button class="draw-tool-btn" title="Reset zoom"><i data-lucide="scan"></i></button>
              <span class="canvas-zoom">100%</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="canvas-surface canvas-surface--svg">
            <IslandMap Mode="neutral">
              @* Authored blue-green monument (green, bright) orbits 1:1 to the other 3 wools — SAME rotated
                 positions, but the captor is DERIVED, so each gets a different colour (green → red, yellow,
                 blue), since a wool is never captured by its own team. Dashed violet ring = orbited. *@
              <circle cx="146" cy="56" r="2.3" fill="#FF5555" opacity="0.85" />
              <circle cx="146" cy="56" r="4.6" fill="none" stroke="var(--canvas-axis)" stroke-width="0.6" stroke-dasharray="2 1.5" opacity="0.8" />
              <circle cx="56" cy="110" r="2.3" fill="#FFFF55" opacity="0.85" />
              <circle cx="56" cy="110" r="4.6" fill="none" stroke="var(--canvas-axis)" stroke-width="0.6" stroke-dasharray="2 1.5" opacity="0.8" />
              <circle cx="110" cy="200" r="2.3" fill="#5555FF" opacity="0.85" />
              <circle cx="110" cy="200" r="4.6" fill="none" stroke="var(--canvas-axis)" stroke-width="0.6" stroke-dasharray="2 1.5" opacity="0.8" />
              <circle cx="200" cy="146" r="2.8" fill="#55FF55" stroke="white" stroke-width="0.8" />
